      Allows logon to a counterparty which does not specify the EncryptMethod (tag98) in its Logon response message.

      Allows the processing of RawData fields (tag96) which do not have a corresponding RawDataLength field (tag95).

      Accept any Logon message.

      DIALECT_CUSTOM_RESEND_REQUEST_MAX_GAP
      If true application could implement custom max gap handling.

      Determines whether or not the session logs out and disconnects when there is no response during the resend timeout period.
      DIALECT_DO_NOT_SEND_TARGET_COMP_ID
      Determines whether the TargetCompID (tag56) is removed from every outgoing message.
      DIALECT_DONT_SEND_POSS_DUP_FLAG
      Disables the setting of PossDupFlag (tag43) in messages that have been sent previously.
      DIALECT_ENABLE_SHORT_TEST_REQ_ID_FORMAT
      Determines the format of the TestReqID (tag112).
      DIALECT_HANDLE_MISSING_POSS_DUP_ON_GAP_FILL
      Accepts SequenceReset/GapFill messages without the PossDupFlag (tag43).
      DIALECT_IGNORE_BEGIN_STRING
      Accept messages where FIX version given in the BeginString (tag8) does not match that configured for the session.
      DIALECT_IGNORE_COMPANY_ID
      Determines whether SenderCompID (tag49) and TargetCompID (tag56) are validated over the course of a FIX session.
      DIALECT_IGNORE_EMPTY_TAGS
      Allows messages with fields which have a tag and not a value.
      DIALECT_IGNORE_ID_FIELDS_IN_LOGON_RESPONSE
      Determines whether the party ID fields (CompID, SubID, LocationID) that are returned in a Logon message are used.
      DIALECT_IGNORE_INPUT_MESSAGE_SEQUENCING
      Determines whether input messages are processed immediately even if they are out of sequence.
      DIALECT_IGNORE_TAG_ORDERING
      Allow non-compliant ordering of tags in FIX message.
      DIALECT_IGNORE_TIMESTAMP_FORMAT
      Allows messages with non-standard timestamp formats.
      DIALECT_INITIALIZE_CIPHER_ONCE_PER_SESSION
      Determines whether, when using Encryption, the cipher is initialised once at the beginning of each session, or for every FIX message.
      DIALECT_INSERT_CUSTOM_FIELDS_IN_HEADER
      Configures custom fields to be sent in the header of every FIX message, in configurations where a counterparty is expecting those custom fields.
      DIALECT_NUMERIC_SENDING_TIME
      Determines whether SendingTime (tag52) and OrigSendingTime (tag122) are sent as numeric values rather than FIX format date strings.
      DIALECT_ORIG_SENDING_TIME_IN_GAP_FILL
      Determines whether the OrigSendingTime (tag122) is added to gap fill messages.
      DIALECT_PROCESS_SKIPPED_MESSAGES
      Determines whether messages skipped as a result of a Sequence Reset or a Gap Fill should be processed if they have been received.
      DIALECT_RESEND_REQUEST_END_SEQ_NO_ALWAYS_INFINITY
      Determines the value of the EndSeqNo (tag16) in ResendRequest messages.
      DIALECT_SEND_NEXT_EXPECTED_MSG_SEQ_NUM_ON_LOGIN
      Determines whether NextExpectedSeqNum (tag789) is added to outgoing Logon messages.

      Determines whether the NewSeqNo (tag36) in a SequenceReset message is interpretted as the last sequence number received.

      If greater than zero, CameronFIX limits message gap range in ResendRequest to this value.
